HEADWORD: Stiver
<hw>Sti"ver</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D.
<ets>stuiver</ets>; akin to G. <ets>st⟦uum⟧ber</ets>, Dan.
<ets>styver</ets>, Sw. <ets>styfver</ets>.]</ety> <def>A Dutch coin, and
money of account, of the value of two cents, or about one penny
sterling; hence, figuratively, anything of little worth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

